main event: A bright object was reported moving rapidly and disappearing over Philadelphia, Pennsylvania on August 25, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as being circular or saucer-shaped, with lights or other objects on the outside that were a fuchsia color.
The object appeared to flash or give off a light when passing a visible airplane.
The object's motion was reported as erratic, maneuvering quickly and moving faster than a jet plane.
The witness compared the size of the object to the diameter of a dinner plate held at arm's length.
The object left a trail that quickly dissipated as it moved across the sky.
sighted object: a bright, circular or saucer-shaped object with lights on the outside
